ews of Songshu and Liangshu referred to ___ as She-po .","wiki"),("oils","4","An oil is any nonpolar chemical substance that is a viscous liquid at ambient temperatures and is both hydrophobic . ___ have a high carbon and hydrogen content and are usually flammable and surface active.","wiki"),("sour","4","Taste receptors in the mouth sense the five taste modalities: sweetness, ___ness, saltiness,  bitterness, and savoriness .","wiki"),("ions","4","An ion , the net charge of an ion is non-zero due to its total number of electrons being unequal to its total number of protons.  A cation is a positively charged ion, with more protons than electrons, while an anion is negatively charged, with more electrons than protons. Because of their opposite electric charges, cat___ and an___ attract each other and readily form ionic compounds.","wiki"),("thai","4","___ cuisine  is the national cuisine of ___land.","wiki"),("meal","4","A ___ is an eating occasion that takes place at a certain time and includes prepared food. The names used for specific ___s in English vary, depending on the speaker's culture, the time of day, or the size of the ___.","wiki"),("list","4","This is a ___ of African cuisines. A cuisine is a characteristic style of cooking practices and traditions,","wiki"),("meze","4","___ or mezze  is a selection of small dishes served as appetizers in parts of the Middle East, the Balkans, Greece, and North Africa. In some Middle Eastern and African regions where it is present, especially predominantly Muslim regions where alcohol is less common, ___ is often served as a part of multi-course meals, while in Greece, Turkey, and the Balkans, they function more as snacks while drinking or talking.","wiki"),("soul","4","This is a list of ___ foods and dishes. ___ food is a style of cuisine that is associated with African Americans in the Southern United States","wiki"),("plum","4","This is a list of ___ dishes. ___ dishes are those that use ___s or prunes as a primary ingredient. Some ___ dishes also use other fruits in their preparation. ___ and prune snack foods and beverages are also included in this list.","wiki"),("clam","4","This is a list of ___ dishes and foods, which are prepared using ___s as a primary ingredient. Edible ___s can be eaten raw, steamed, boiled, baked or fried.","wiki"),("crab","4","This is a list of ___ dishes. ___s live in all the world's oceans, in fresh water, and on land, are generally covered with a thick exoskeleton and are arthropoda and have a single pair of claws. ___ meat is the meat found within a ___. It is used in many cuisines across the world.","wiki"),("veal","4","This is a list of ___ dishes, which use or may use ___ as a primary ingredient. ___ is the meat of young cows, in contrast to the beef from older cattle. Though ___ can be produced from a cow of either sex and any breed, most ___ comes from male cows. Generally, ___ is more expensive than beef from older cattle.","wiki"),("goat","4","This is a list of ___ dishes, which use ___ meat as a primary ingredient. ___ meat is the meat of the domestic ___ . It is often called chevon or mutton when the meat comes from adults, and cabrito, capretto, or kid when from young animals. Worldwide, ___ meat is less widely consumed than pork, beef, and poultry.","wiki"),("lamb","4","This is a list of ___ and mutton dishes and foods. ___ and mutton are terms for the meat of domestic sheep  at different ages. A sheep in its first year is called a ___, and its meat is also called ___. The meat of a juvenile sheep older than one year is hogget; outside North America this is also a term for the living animal.  The meat of an adult sheep is mutton, a term only used for the meat, not the living animal.","wiki"),("hams","4","This is a list of notable ___ and ham products. Ham is pork that has been preserved through salting, smoking, or wet curing. Ham is made around the world, including a number of highly coveted regional specialties, such as Westphalian ham