or aquaculture. A ___ may include macroscopic fungus .","wiki"),("beer","4","___ is one of the oldest","wiki"),("wine","4","___ is an alcoholic drink typically made from fermented grapes. Yeast consumes the sugar in the grapes and converts it to ethanol, carbon dioxide, and heat. Different varieties of grapes and strains of yeasts produce different styles of ___. These variations result from the complex interactions between the biochemical development of the grape, the reactions involved in fermentation, the grape's growing environment , and the production process. Many countries enact legal appellations intended to define styles and qualities of ___. These typically restrict the geographical origin and permitted varieties of grapes, as well as other aspects of ___ production. ___s not made from grapes involve fermentation of additional crops including,  rice ___ and other fruit ___s such as plum, cherry, pomegranate, currant and elderberry.","wiki"),("maga","4","Thespesia grandiflora is a tree in the family Malvaceae of the rosids clade.","wiki"),("luau","4","A lūʻau , poke, lomi salmon, ʻopihi, and haupia, beer, and entertainment such as traditional Hawaiian music and hula. Among people from Hawaiʻi, the concepts of 'lūʻau' and 'party' are often blended, resulting in graduation lūʻaus, wedding lūʻaus, and birthday lūʻaus.","wiki"),("pies","4","A pie is a baked dish which is usually made of a pastry dough casing that contains a filling of various sweet or savoury ingredients. Sweet ___ may be filled with fruit .","wiki"),("stew","4","A ___ is a combination of solid food ingredients that have been cooked in liquid and served in the resultant gravy. Ingredients in a ___ can include any combination of vegetables , allowing flavours to mingle.","wiki"),("lard","4","___ is fat from a pig, in both its rendered and unrendered forms. It is a semi-soft white fat derived from fatty parts of the pig, with a high saturated fatty acid content and no trans fat. Rendering is by s