ugh it has naturalized in many places throughout the world. It has a long history of medicinal and culinary use, and in modern times as an ornamental garden plant. The common name '___' is also used for a number of related and unrelated species.","wiki"),("star","4","Illicium verum is a medium-sized evergreen tree native to northeast Vietnam and southwest China. A spice commonly called ___ anise, ___anise, ___ anise seed, Chinese ___ anise, or badian that closely resembles anise in flavor is obtained from the ___-shaped pericarps of the fruit of I. verum which are harvested just before ripening. ___ anise oil is a highly fragrant oil used in cooking, perfumery, soaps, toothpastes, mouthwashes, and skin creams. About 90% of the world's ___ anise crop is used for extraction of shikimic acid, a chemical intermediate used in the synthesis of oseltamivir .","wiki"),("blue","4","Trigonella caerulea ","wiki"),("soft","4","___wood is usually wood from gymnosperm trees such as pines and spruces. ___woods are not necessarily ___er than hardwoods. In both groups there is an enormous variation in actual wood hardness, the range of density in hardwoods completely including that of ___woods.  Some hardwoods  are ___er than most ___woods, while the hardest hardwoods are much harder than any ___wood. The woods of longleaf pine, Douglas fir, and yew are much harder in the mechanical sense than several hardwoods.","wiki"),("rimu","4","Dacrydium cupressinum, commonly known as ___, is a large evergreen coniferous tree endemic to the forests of New Zealand. It is a member of the southern conifer group, the podocarps. The former name 'red pine' has fallen out of common use.","wiki"),("hard","4","___woods are produced by angiosperm trees that reproduce by flowers, and have broad leaves. Many species are deciduous. Those of temperate regions lose their leaves every autumn as temperatures fall and are dormant in the winter, but those of tropical regions may shed their leaves in response to 