cies, with approximately 90 occurring in the United States, while Mexico has 160 species of which 109 are endemic. The second greatest center of oak diversity is China, which contains approximately 100 species.","wiki"),("skis","4","A ski is a narrow strip of semi-rigid material worn underfoot to glide over snow.  Substantially longer than wide and characteristically employed in pairs, ___ are attached to ski boots with ski bindings, with either a free, lockable, or partially secured heel. For climbing slopes, ski skins  can be attached at the base of the ski.","wiki"),("burl","4","A ___  is a tree growth in which the grain has grown in a deformed manner. It is commonly found in the form of a rounded outgrowth on a tree trunk or branch that is filled with small knots from dormant buds.","wiki"),("lath","4","A ___ or slat is a thin, narrow strip of straight-grained wood used under roof shingles or tiles, on ___ and plaster walls and ceilings to hold plaster, and in lattice and trellis work.","wiki"),("sill","4","A ___ plate or sole plate in construction and architecture is the bottom horizontal member of a wall or building to which vertical members are attached. The word plate is typically omitted in America and carpenters speak simply of the '___'. Other names are ground plate, ground ___, groundsel, and midnight ___. ___ plates are usually composed of lumber but can be any material. The timber at the top of a wall is often called a top plate, pole plate, wall plate or simply 'the plate'.","wiki"),("stud","4","A wall ___ is a vertical framing member in a building's wall of smaller cross section than a post. They are a fundamental element in frame building.","wiki"),("nano","4","___cellulose is a term referring to ___-structured cellulose. This may be either cellulose ___crystal ,  or bacterial ___cellulose, which refers to ___-structured cellulose produced by bacteria.","wiki"),("dyes","4","A dyewood is any of a number of varieties of wood which provide ___ for text